</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umalloy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Malloy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(6/14/01 8:54:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=246.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/in_virtue/danumbaone.jpg border=0></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Advice on Talendor please? :)</span><hr size=1> Spend your mana on making sure most, if not everyone had dammage shield on.  Im sure that you know how good of a FR buff DS is.  As for using a pet, use the 49 fire one,  Its your best shot if you want to use a pet for this fight.  The +50 pets are not immune to fire, and suck... so dont even bother with thoes. <p>_iGrum b00tsy_ <BR>
Gnomish brother<BR>
......hi there......<BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucydmab.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cydmab</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#333333>(6/14/01 9:50:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=246.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Advice on Talendor please? :)</span><hr size=1> While we are asking for advice, does tale charm? Once we had several pets go rogue when fighting him. The pets went right for the clerics. It was bad. I wasn't sure if the dragon charmed them or there was some strange bug associated with fear. <p>
