<br>
Folks, please stop giving wrong advice if you don't know...<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukylere.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kylere</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 113<br> <font color=#333333>(6/14/01 3:05:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=246.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Advice on Talendor please? :)</span><hr size=1> I always use my pet when we kill him. Fearing for adds is not really an issue if you pull him to an out of the way corner. We generally leave someone on the BW side of the SF/BW zoneline as a town cryer to warn people, and pull him to that zone. <br>
<br>
To be honest though, outside of damage shields and the accompanying FR we are not all that effective ( at least not at my level) vs him. The pet pops off some hits between fears and you should have annul up for removing that outrageous DoT he throws on people ( most people hate dying after the mob does heh).<br>
<br>
Of course it is always wise to have your pet MR'd the best you can, I usually have a cleric or druid toss a buff on him and i give him daggers of symbols ( not sure if they have an effect on his MR, but they are cheap to summon so no loss if they do not) <p>Kylere Ap'Kailere -Mage of 57 Summers<BR>
Kailere Drowsbane of Veeshan -Paladin of 55 summers<BR>
Kailyre Ap'Kailere -Portwhore of 48 Summers (acct 2)<BR>
Celestial Tomb<BR>
In difficult ground, press on; In encircled ground, devise strategems; In death ground, FIGHT! - Sun Tzu</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usambus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sambus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#333333>(6/14/01 3:23:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=246.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.shiftclick.net/eq/sigs/60x60tinker.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Advice on Talendor please? :)</span><hr size=1> In my experience, until 59 when you get Valiant Companion, mages are pretty worthless against Talendor.  You'll basically spend all your mana making mod rods beforehand, and keeping all the tanks damage shielded for the extra FR.<br>
<br>
He has an AE fire DoT and AE fear.  Unless you have Dyzil's you'll be using your 49 fire pet, and it'll get feared every time.  Since he's a fire dragon with high MR, both our lines of nukes aren't going to do much (you *may* be able to scratch him after tash/malo at higher levels, I don't know).<br>
<br>
At my level, about the best I can do is to park my pet at the pull-to spot, DS everyone, and go sit up on the side of a mountain and watch the fireworks down below.  Then once the fight is over, race down and start dispelling everyone who's DoT'd. <p><font face="Verdana">
<small><small>[55 Conjurer] <b><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=25780">Sambus</a></b> (Gnome) <<a
href="http://pub44.ezboard.com/blordsofthedragon54523">Lords of the Dragon</a>> ZONE: Mithaniel Marr
</small></small></font><br><br>

<img src="http://www.shiftclick.net/eq/sigs/sig4.jpg" alt="The Wise.">
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukaemon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaemon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#333333>(6/14/01 3:23:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=246.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Advice on Talendor please? :)</span><hr size=1> All Fire Vocerate's are immuned to fire. <p>Kaemon<br>Arch Mage of the Nameless<br><a href=http://www.Shockofswords.com>Shock of Swords</a><br>
<br><a href="http://www.shockofswords.homestead.com/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.shockofswords.homestead.com/files/petfoff.jpg" border="0"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucobeeblazesummoner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cobee Blazesummoner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#333333>(6/14/01 4:06:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=246.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Advice on Talendor please? :)</span><hr size=1> From my experience with Talendor, his fire AE is virtually unresistable.  We had level 55-60 people at the last attempt I attended with FR over 200, and they were getting the full blast each time.  At one point, the only thing I could see attacking him was a mage's fire pet with Valiant Companion cast on it because everyone else was feared.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Otherwise, it's almost useless to try to send a pet at him, IMO.  It just gets feared and slain quickly by melee.  Being the stubborn mage I am, though, I'll still be making a pet and claiming it was useful.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center><a href="http://home.earthlink.net/~abspara/index.htm"><img src=http://roxorzjoo.homestead.com/files/corpse1mod.gif border=no></a><br><i>Magi of the 52nd re-ding</i></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uceledra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Celedra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#333333>(6/14/01 9:40:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=246.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://personal.lig.bellsouth.net/lig/g/_/g_daspit/variasig1.jpg width=160 height=120></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Advice on Talendor please? :)</span><hr size=1> I haven't played any in just over a month, but I think these ideas should work just fine unless something was changed.  I wasn't able to nuke him, but that was without a malo on him (did have mala though).  A fire DS isn't bad to have since I have resisted his AE dot before, but they still land a lot with a 240+ FR at level 60.  I wouldn't use the 52 or 58 fire pets since they like to cast crap wizard spells and hit for very little.  Instead I'd use either the 49 fire pet or the non fire vocarate/greater vocaration spells.  I know the non fire pets will be hit hard by his AE breath weapon, but if you have some extra mana left over after the DS then this is an idea.  The post 50 pets do more damage in general than their 49th level brothers.  This is assuming you aren't summoning mod rods for the fight.  The times I've fought him, the wasn't any demand for the mod rods.  You can resummon your post 50 pets as they die.  I'm not sure if the additional damage done by a 49 fire/decoy during the resummon time is enough to counter the extra melee abilities that the vocarate/greater vocaration pets have.<br>
<br>
Just my thoughts.<br>
<br>
Varia <p><center><img src="http://putrescence.org/symphony/Variasig.jpg"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uaamilae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aamilae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#333333>(6/14/01 9:56:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=246.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Advice on Talendor please? :)</span><hr size=1> While not immune to fire the epic performs fine to.  Combined with Valiant Companion as Sambus pointed out you can really start to feel useful.<br>
<br>
After Malo + bard + tash I've never been able to land a magic nuke.<br>
<br>
Personally I don't worry about doing ds on anyone but my group and tanks.  Reason being that by time you can get to anyone 1/2 of the shields are already gone.<br>
 <p><br><a href="http://www.noows.com/modules.php?op=modload&name=EverQuest_Profiles&file=index&show=632&letter=&filter_server=&filter_race=&filter_class=&order="><img src="http://presys.com/~thepub/images/aamilae%20banadar%20sig.gif" border=no></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uvanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vanz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#333333>(6/14/01 11:19:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=246.topic&index=10>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Advice on Talendor please? :)</span><hr size=1> Hey Cobee, that was my fire pet you saw.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Most everyone here is correct though.  You have little (more like no chance) to land a spell on Talendor.  I've yet to land a spell other than Mala on him.  Valiant Companion is a blessing and a curse at times.  Try not to send your pet in immediately if you have Valiant Companion.  Since Talendor cannot be slowed the tanks that aren't feared sometimes die pretty quickly and then your pet builds up some decent aggro resulting in &quot;You have been summoned&quot; ... LOADING, PLEASE WAIT.<br>
<br>
Damage shield those that you can prior to the fight.  Try and recast your pet if it dies and refresh the damage shield on those that are still alive.  That's about the only thing you can really do.<br>
<br>
